---
title: Redacted Text
description: "Sensitive text blurred by default and revealed on hover using CSS `filter: blur()` — no JavaScript."
slug: redacted-text
cssFile: redacted-text.css
explanation: "`filter: blur()` is applied to inline `<span>` elements wrapping the sensitive words. The `transition` property smoothly animates the blur to `0` on `:hover`. `user-select: none` prevents copying the blurred text without revealing it first. This is a pure CSS privacy pattern — great for previewing redacted documents, hiding spoilers, or masking sensitive data in screenshots."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="demo-redacted-text">
	<p>Project <span class="redacted">Nightfall</span> is our internal codename for the upcoming acquisition of <span class="redacted">Meridian Labs</span>. The deal is expected to close on <span class="redacted">March 14th</span> for a total of <span class="redacted">$240 million</span>.</p>
	<p>The lead negotiator is <span class="redacted">Sarah Chen</span> from our legal team. Her direct contact is <span class="redacted">sarah@example.com</span> — please keep this confidential until the public announcement.</p>
	<span class="hint">// hover to reveal</span>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<p>
  Project <span class="redacted">Nightfall</span> is our
  internal codename for the acquisition of
  <span class="redacted">Meridian Labs</span>.
</p>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.redacted {
  filter: blur(5px);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: filter .4s ease;
  user-select: none;
}

.redacted:hover {
  filter: blur(0);
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
